        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(cloudflare): advertise FeatureRunSession + return run-session handle",
        "body": "Implements the Cloudflare provider slice of the run-session adoption tracker #182.\n\n## What changed\n- Advertise `core.FeatureRunSession` for `cloudflare`.\n- Return a `RunSessionHandle` from every post-identity run path.\n- Keep `RunID` empty because Cloudflare has a lease identity but no distinct execution-run identity.\n- Emit a shell-quoted cleanup command: `crabbox stop --provider cloudflare --id <lease-id>`.\n- Add keep, keep-on-failure, cleanup quoting, provider-spec, docs, and changelog coverage.\n\n## Live Cloudflare proof\nValidated against a deployed Cloudflare Container Worker with an ephemeral bearer secret, removed immediately after the test:\n\n```sh\ncrabbox run \\\n  --provider cloudflare \\\n  --type lite \\\n  --keep \\\n  --lease-output /tmp/cloudflare-session.json \\\n  --no-sync \\\n  --timing-json \\\n  -- true\n```\n\nObserved redacted handle:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"provider\": \"cloudflare\",\n  \"leaseId\": \"<redacted>\",\n  \"slug\": \"<redacted>\",\n  \"reused\": false,\n  \"kept\": true,\n  \"cleanupCommand\": \"crabbox stop --provider cloudflare --id '<redacted>'\"\n}\n```\n\n`runId` was absent as intended. Executing the emitted cleanup command stopped the exact retained container successfully. Afterward the temporary Worker secret was deleted and readiness returned to its original `503 runner token is not configured` state.\n\n## Verification\n- `go test -race ./internal/providers/cloudflare`\n- `go test ./internal/cli -run 'Test.*(LeaseOutput|RunLease|RunSession|Cloudflare)' -count=1`\n- `go vet ./internal/providers/cloudflare ./internal/cli`\n- Codex autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\nMaintainer fixup: 2c4a3e25.\n\nThanks @zozo123.",
